# LLM & AI Integration

## Tiered LLM Architecture (openai_client.py)

Two cloud providers with auto-escalation:

| Tier | Provider | Default Model | Env Vars |
|------|----------|---------------|----------|
| Primary (free) | Groq | llama-3.3-70b-versatile | `LLM_API_KEY`, `LLM_MODEL`, `LLM_BASE_URL` |
| Fallback (free) | Gemini | gemini-2.0-flash | `PREMIUM_API_KEY`, `PREMIUM_MODEL`, `PREMIUM_BASE_URL` |

**Auto-escalation**: primary â†’ check quality (`_is_weak_response`) â†’ fallback if weak.

Both `chat()` and `chat_stream()` use the OpenAI-compatible API pattern:

```python
client = OpenAI(api_key=api_key, base_url=base_url)
response = client.chat.completions.create(model=model, messages=messages)
```

## LLM Caller (services/llm_caller.py)

Thin wrapper for services that need LLM calls without importing `chat_service` (avoids circular deps):

```python
from ..llm_caller import call_llm
reply = call_llm(messages=[{"role": "user", "content": prompt}], max_tokens=800)
```

